  "prompt": "How do you treat acne on your arms?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to treat acne on your arms:\n\n1. Cleansing\n- Use a gentle, non-comedogenic body wash\n- Wash arms daily with lukewarm water\n- Avoid scrubbing too hard\n\n2. Topical treatments\n- Benzoyl peroxide\n- Salicylic acid\n- Tea tree oil\n- Over-the-counter acne creams\n\n3. Exfoliation\n- Use a gentle exfoliating scrub 1-2 times per week\n- Remove dead skin cells\n- Prevent clogged pores\n\n4. Moisturizing\n- Use oil-free, non-comedogenic moisturizer\n- Keep skin hydrated\n- Prevent excess oil production\n\n5. Clothing and hygiene\n- Wear loose, breathable clothing\n- Change clothes after sweating\n- Use clean towels\n- Avoid touching arms with dirty hands\n\n6. Medical treatments\n- Prescription topical medications\n- Oral antibiotics\n- Consult a dermatologist for severe cases\n\n7. Lifestyle changes\n- Maintain a healthy diet\n- Stay hydrated\n- Manage stress\n- Get enough sleep\n\nIf arm acne persists or worsens, consult a healthcare professional for personalized treatment.",
